            "validate": true,
            "highlightUI": "jsEditor"
        },
        {
            "title": "Start the repeating timer",
            "image": "/static/tutorials/steps/jsTimers_05_startInterval.webp",
            "imageFocus": {
                "x": 45,
                "y": 50,
                "zoom": 1.2
            },
            "narration": {
                "id": "gui.tutorials.jsTimers.startInterval",
                "default": "Drag a repeat every block. Set the number to one thousand. JavaScript timers count in MILLISECONDS — one thousand of them is one second. The body runs once per second. Unlike Scratch's wait, this does not pause anything else."
            },
            "highlightUI": "jsEditor"
        },
        {
            "title": "Bump and show",
            "image": "/static/tutorials/steps/jsTimers_06_bumpAndShow.webp",
            "imageFocus": {
                "x": 45,
                "y": 50,
                "zoom": 1.2
            },
            "narration": {
                "id": "gui.tutorials.jsTimers.bumpAndShow",
                "default": "Inside repeat every — a change by block. Variable seconds. Amount one. Then a set text of block. Element is clock. Text is a join of Seconds, a space, and seconds. The number ticks on the page."
            },
            "highlightUI": "jsEditor"
        },
        {
            "title": "Save the timer id",
            "image": "/static/tutorials/steps/jsTimers_07_saveId.webp",
            "imageFocus": {
                "x": 45,
                "y": 50,
                "zoom": 1.2
            },
            "narration": {
                "id": "gui.tutorials.jsTimers.saveId",
                "default": "Right after the repeat every block, add a const named timerId. Value is the last interval id reporter. Every JS timer has an id. Save it now because you need it to cancel later."
            },
            "highlightUI": "jsEditor"
        },
        {
            "title": "Stop after ten",
            "image": "/static/tutorials/steps/jsTimers_08_stopAfterTen.webp",
            "imageFocus": {
                "x": 45,
                "y": 50,
                "zoom": 1.2
            },
            "narration": {
                "id": "gui.tutorials.jsTimers.stopAfterTen",
                "default": "Inside the repeat every body, after the update, add an if block. Condition — seconds triple-equals ten. Inside — a cancel interval block with timerId. Then a set text of on clock with the value Seconds ten done."
            },
            "highlightUI": "jsEditor"
        },
        {
            "title": "Save and watch",
